  "response": "Yes, it absolutely goes without saying that **money laundering** is illegal. Money laundering is the process of disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. This is done to make the money appear as if it comes from a legitimate source. \n\nAlmost every country in the world has strict laws and regulations to combat money laundering, as it is often associated with criminal activities such as drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, and terrorism financing. Penalties for money laundering can include heavy fines, asset forfeiture, and significant prison sentences. \n\nEfforts to prevent money laundering are crucial for maintaining the integrity of financial systems and combating organized crime globally.",
